BT /F3 18 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 730 Tm (Preface) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 696 Tm (This book is meant to be easy to follow.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 682 Tm (You do not need to know Puff already. If you have written a little code in ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 668 Tm (another language, that is enough. The book explains what the main parts of ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 654 Tm (Puff are, how a project is laid out, and how to read and write simple programs) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 640 Tm ( without assuming deep compiler knowledge.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 626 Tm (Puff is the name of the CLI you use day to day. `pinggen` is still the ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 612 Tm (compiler and repository name you will see in source paths and internal docs. ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 598 Tm (In normal use, you create, build, and run programs with `puff`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 584 Tm (Everything in this book is based on features that exist in the repository now.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 570 Tm ( It does not describe planned features as if they already work.) Tj ET
BT /F3 18 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 556 Tm (Who This Book Is For) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 522 Tm (This book is for:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 508 Tm (- beginners who want a gentle first pass through the language) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 494 Tm (- programmers coming from another language who want to learn Puff quickly) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 480 Tm (- anyone who wants one document that explains both the language and the usual ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 466 Tm (  project workflow) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 452 Tm (This book is not a formal language specification. It is a practical guide.) Tj ET
BT /F3 18 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 438 Tm (How To Use This Book) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 404 Tm (If you are brand new to Puff, read the chapters in order.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 390 Tm (If you already know the basics, you can jump straight to:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 376 Tm (- modules and dependencies) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 362 Tm (- vectors with `Vec<T>`) Tj ET
