BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 334 Tm (- the reference appendix) Tj ET
BT /F3 18 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 320 Tm (1. What Puff Is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 286 Tm (Puff is a small compiled language for practical command-line programs.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 272 Tm (You write source files with the `.pg` extension. Puff reads those files, ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 258 Tm (checks them, lowers them through LLVM IR, and builds a native executable.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 298 32 Tm (3) Tj ET
endstream
